content:
Great, if your Laravel project name is "webgem", you can navigate to the project directory by running the following command in the terminal:
```bash
cd webgem
```
After navigating to the project directory, you can continue with the steps mentioned in my previous answer.

For example, you can open your Laravel project in VS Code editor by running the following command:
```css
code .
```
This will open your Laravel project in VS Code editor.

Similarly, you can configure your database, set up your application key, create routes, views, and test your application using the commands mentioned in my previous answer.

Just make sure to run the commands from within the "webgem" project directory in the terminal.
